  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1988-03-09", 
    "text": "Aviation Whistleblower Protection Act of 1988 - Amends the Federal Aviation Act of 1958 to prohibit discriminatory adverse actions by an aviation industry employer against an employee who has alerted Federal officials to civil aircraft safety hazards, if such employee had previously disclosed the same information to his employer. Sets forth a grievance and investigation procedure for violations of this Act."
  }, 
